# Scanner TypeScript Conventions

## Module layout

- One concern per file under `src/scanner/`
- Shared types in `scanner.types.ts`; thresholds and selectors in `shared/constants.ts`
- Use ESM imports with `.js` extension: `import { x } from './foo.js'`

## Locator generation

- Prefer `data-testid` XPath: `//tag[@data-testid="..."]`
- Use relational XPaths (ancestor-scoped, label-sibling) to disambiguate duplicate generic testIds
- Use `directText` (immediate text nodes), not full `textContent` subtree
- Rank variants in `rank-xpath-variants.ts`; validate uniqueness on the live page before saving
- Skip unstable/hash CSS classes via `xpath-utils.ts`

## DOM extraction

- Batch work in `page.evaluate()` where possible — avoid per-element round-trips
- `extract-element-context.ts` collects ancestors, label siblings, and extended attributes in one pass

## Registry

- Save to `registry/{scanName}.json` via `save-registry.ts`
- Keys generated by `generate-key.ts` using testId + ancestor context for generic IDs

## Changes

- Keep diffs minimal; match existing naming and patterns
- Add or update unit tests in `tests/scanner.spec.ts` for non-trivial logic
